description:
• Location
  • Severity
  • Quality
  • Timing : Constant / Intermittent, how long did it last

  • Associated Signs or Symptoms

description: Record viral load 6months after the treatment started and then repeat once in every 12 months.

description: If patients switched from first line to second line, then record the switched date here.

description: If patient's regimen is changed or substituted, record the date.

description: Description: those who is diagnosed with OI (new diagnosis). Sometime follow case (patient on ART) also has new OI diagnosis who was previously being treated to other OI.
